IRS990.MissionDesc: THE COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER IS COMMITTED TO PROVIDING ACCESS TO QUALITY
IRS990.Desc: THE COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER WAS ESTABLISHED TO PROVIDE QUALITY, AFFORDABLE HEALTH CARE TO THE LOCAL COMMUNITY. THE COMPREHENSIVE SERVICES INCLUDE PRIMARY OUTPATIENT MEDICAL CARE, OBSTETRICS, GYNECOLOGY, DIAGNOSTIC SERVICES, NUTRITION SERVICES, BEHAVIOR HEALTH SERVICES, EDUCATION AND PREVENTION PROGRAMS AS WELL AS OTHER SUPPORTING SERVICES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: TITLE X - FAMILY PLANNING SERVICES PROVIDING MATERNAL/CHILD PRIMARY HEALTH CARE SERVICES, OBSTETRICS, GYNECOLOGY, CASE MANAGEMENT, HEALTH EDUCATION AND FAMILY PLANNING COUNSELING TO PREGNANT WOMEN AND THEIR FAMILIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: THE CHICAGO FAMILY CASE MANAGEMENT PROGRAM PROVIDES A COMPREHENSIVE ARRAY OF MATERNAL AND CHILD HEALTH SERVICES TO PREGNANT WOMEN AND INFANTS UP TO TWELVE MONTHS OF AGE, INCLUDING CASE MANAGEMENT, OUTREACH AND TRANSPORTATION.

The Organization makes all governing documents,conflict of interest policies and financial statements available upon request.

The members must disclose if there is a conflict of interest at the annual Board Meeting. The Board Members complete and sign a form documenting that at the time there are no conflicts of interest. Each year the board members sign a new form and if there is a conflict the member abstains from voting. If a board member is found to have not disclosed a conflict, the member will be brought before the executive committee.
The Board of Directors Reviews Annually, the compensation of the CEO.
The CEO Evaluates compensation of employees every two years.
Due to time constrains, a copy of Form 990 will be provided to the board at the next board meeting.
